
Fall 2025 Progress Report
===============================================================================



1. Project Status
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

By the numbers - Over 9000 commits!

v0.2: 2913 commits, 2142 of those being since the last blog post, so there's a lot of new stuff to talk about here.

version 0.2.64 as of October 2025, we've kept pace with weekly relases over the summer, and a longer but still frequent release cadance over the academic semesters. The last blog post was at v0.2.29. So again, lots to cover.

AI Use in Mech

As a solo developer, I have been using AI in the process of making mech and it has accelerated my output. You can see the effect of that in the commit history, where I have been able to make more frequent releases and implement more features in a shorter amount of time. I plan to write a blog post about my experience using AI in software development soon.

Capstone Team

Project team includes myself, and this year we have a capstone team of 4 computer science students from Lehigh University helping to build out the standard library. We'll have a follow up post about that.

